    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 1993 Mazda RX-7 (FD3S) remains a purist\u2019s benchmark for balanced dynamics. Powered by the sequential twin-turbocharged 13B-REW rotary, the engine maintains excellent compression across both rotors. The chassis features the original four-wheel double-wishbone suspension, providing exceptional kinesthetics and a perfect 50/50 weight distribution. Recent maintenance includes a comprehensive refresh of the complex vacuum hose 'rat's nest' to ensure seamless turbo transition. The five-speed manual gearbox shifts precisely with healthy synchros, delivering power to the rear wheels via the factory Torsen limited-slip differential. While showing minor cosmetic patina consistent with its age, the mechanical integrity and structural rigidity of this FD remain uncompromised.",
